<p>There&#8217;s dark brown sugar &#8212; and there&#8217;s dark muscovado brown sugar! Much darker and perfect for the sugared bacon method you suggest. See: Browner Sugar: <a href="http://feedme.typepad.com/my_weblog/2010/08/browner-sugar.html" rel="nofollow">http://feedme.typepad.com/my_weblog/2010/08/browner-sugar.html</a></p>
<p>The other name for the bacon + brown sugar recipe is Pig Candy! Coat bacon with brown sugar and bake. Add ground pecans for a praline version.</p>
