					<dt class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-115749">
<span class="avatar"></span>
<span class="comment_num"><a href="#comment-115749" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">67</a></span>
<span class="comment_author">Dallas</span>
<span class="comment_time">September 22, 2010 at 5:09 pm</span>

					</dt>
					<dd class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-115749">
<p>I can&#8217;t believe no one had mentioned my personal favorite&#8230;..chocolate covered bacon!  Your best bet is to use thick-cut bacon and fry it up however you normally would.  Then, cool it in the refrigerator while you melt some chocolate.  Slice each piece of bacon in half and then slice those pieces in half lengthwise.  You should end up with pieces of bacon about length &amp; width of french fries.  One at a time, pick up the bacon by one end and lay it on top of the melted chocolate (still holding it).  Give it a quick flip to coat the other side and set it on waxed paper.  Sprinkle with coarse salt, cool in the fridge, and anticipate munchie nirvana&#8230;mmmmm! :)</p>
</div>
					</dd>
